-- Conergy Says 5.3-Megawatt Solar Plant Connected to Spanish Grid
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-02-16T14:23:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/conergy-says-5-3-megawatt-solar-plant-connected-to-spanish-grid.html
Conergy AG (CGYK)  said a 5.3-megawatt solar
power plant using its products was connected to the grid in
southern  Spain .  Local developers Valfortec and Solaer installed 22,000
Conergy-branded modules manufactured by a supplier at a plant
near the city of Mazarron, the Hamburg-based solar energy
company said today in an e-mailed statement. The developers also
installed 380 inverters and 50 kilometers (31 miles) of racks
manufactured by Conergy, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
 snicola2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
